getSuggestions

private java.util.ArrayList getSuggestions(DMIdentifier node,
                                           java.util.ArrayList names,
                                           int index)
Retrieves completion suggestions. Should be called with the DataMap root node and an index of 0.

Parameters:
node - The node to search. Use the DataMap root.
names - A list of the names to seek through in the DataMap
index - For recursion purposes. Use 0 here.
Returns:
An ArrayList of all possible suggestions.

getDataMap

private DataMap getDataMap()
Retrieves the DataMap we need to look at. First it checks the file's folder for datamap.xdm; if that does not exist, it looks in that folder's parent folder. If there is still no DataMap found, null is returned.

Someday, we should probably keep the reference to the DataMap in order to save on file loading time, but that will require keeping an eye on it for changes, so I'm leaving it out for now.

Returns:
The DataMap to for this file, or null if one could not be found.
